<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,816,1274]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,383,816,842]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Nomenclatural notes</emphasis>
:— 
<bibRefCitation author="Donnell Smith, J." box="[416,663,816,842]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" pagination="417 - 423" refId="ref6270" refString="Donnell Smith, J. (1904) Undescribed plants from Guatemala and other Central American Republics XXVI. Botanical Gazette 37: 417 - 423. https: // doi. org / 10.1086 / 328506" type="journal article" year="1904">Donnell Smith (1904)</bibRefCitation>
cited three gatherings in the protologue with no herbaria specified: 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">von Tuerckheim 8488</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[343,583,852,878]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">von Tuerckheim 7753</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[598,822,852,878]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Donnell Smith 1457</emphasis>
. We traced several specimens in the herbaria F, GH, K, M, 
<collectionCode box="[175,215,889,915]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[273,309,888,914]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">US</collectingCountry>
belonging to the cited gatherings: 
<emphasis box="[696,935,888,914]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">von Tuerckheim 8488</emphasis>
(
<collectingCountry box="[950,987,888,914]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">US</collectingCountry>
barcode 01269192, F barcode 0073066F, M barcode M-0171813, 
<collectionCode box="[408,447,925,951]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
barcode 00138963, 
<collectionCode box="[674,713,925,951]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
barcode 00138964, 
<collectingCountry box="[940,976,924,950]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">US</collectingCountry>
barcode 01014253); 
<emphasis box="[1213,1451,924,950]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">von Tuerckheim 7753</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode box="[144,185,960,986]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
barcode 00138966, 
<collectingCountry box="[418,454,960,986]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">US</collectingCountry>
barcode 01014252, 
<collectingCountry box="[687,723,960,986]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">US</collectingCountry>
barcode 01269193); 
<emphasis box="[967,1194,960,986]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Donnell Smith 1457</emphasis>
(F barcode 0073065F, GH barcode 00077435, K barcode K000585748, 
<collectingCountry box="[689,725,996,1022]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">US</collectingCountry>
barcode 00027445). These specimens completely agree with the protologue and with the current application of the name (
<bibRefCitation author="Benitez de Rojas, C. &amp; D'Arcy, W." box="[779,1179,1032,1058]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" pagination="167 - 310" refId="ref5949" refString="Benitez de Rojas, C. &amp; D'Arcy, W. (1997) The genus Lycianthes (Solanaceae) in Venezuela. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 84: 167 - 310. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2400001" type="journal article" year="1997">Benitez de Rojas and D’Arcy 1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dean, E. &amp; Huerta, M. &amp; Brandon, D." box="[1191,1316,1032,1059]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" pagination="27 - 36" refId="ref6223" refString="Dean, E., Huerta, M. &amp; Brandon, D. (2018) Lycianthes glabripetala (Solanaceae), a new species of series Strigulosae from Queretaro, Mexico. Phytologia (Mar 16, 2018) 100: 27 - 36." type="journal article" year="2018">Dean 2018</bibRefCitation>
) and can be safely considered as original material (Art. 9.3. of the ICN, 
<bibRefCitation author="McNeill, J. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Buck, W. R. &amp; Demoulin, V. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Prud'Homme Van Reine, W. F. &amp; Smith, G. F. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Turland, N. J." box="[805,1030,1068,1095]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" refId="ref6699" refString="McNeill, J., Barrie, F. R., Buck, W. R., Demoulin, V., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Marhold, K., Prado, J., Prud'Homme Van Reine, W. F., Smith, G. F., Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Turland, N. J. (2012) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Melbourne Code) adopted by the Eighteenth International Botanical Congress Melbourne, Australia, July 2011. [Regnum Vegetabile 154]. Gantner, Ruggell, 240 pp." type="book" year="2012">
McNeill 
<emphasis box="[906,955,1068,1094]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">et al</emphasis>
. 2012
</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<emphasis box="[1098,1339,1068,1094]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">von Tuerckheim 8488</emphasis>
specimen at 
<collectingCountry box="[163,199,1104,1130]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">US</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[214,251,1104,1130]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">US</collectingCountry>
barcode 01269192) is selected here as the 
<typeStatus box="[732,835,1104,1130]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">lectotype</typeStatus>
for the name 
<taxonomicName box="[990,1252,1104,1130]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amatitlanense">
<emphasis box="[990,1252,1104,1130]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Solanum amatitlanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,816,1274]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,389,1140,1166]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Taxonomic notes</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bitter" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="J. M. Coult. &amp; Donn. Sm." box="[425,715,1140,1166]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amatitlanensis">
<emphasis box="[425,715,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Lycianthes amatitlanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a member of Bitter’s cohesive series 
<emphasis box="[1140,1268,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Strigulosae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bitter, G." box="[1282,1414,1140,1166]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" pagination="292 - 520" refId="ref6023" refString="Bitter, G. (1919) Die Gattung Lycianthes. Abhandlungen Herausgegeban vom Naturwissenschaftlichen Verein zu Bremen 24: 292 - 520." type="journal article" year="1919">Bitter 1919</bibRefCitation>
), is a small shrub with simple, strigose trichomes that ranges from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[952,1038,1176,1202]" name="Mexico" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Mexico</collectingCountry>
to South America (
<bibRefCitation author="Benitez de Rojas, C. &amp; D'Arcy, W." pageId="1" pageNumber="40" pagination="167 - 310" refId="ref5949" refString="Benitez de Rojas, C. &amp; D'Arcy, W. (1997) The genus Lycianthes (Solanaceae) in Venezuela. Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 84: 167 - 310. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2400001" type="journal article" year="1997">Benítez de Rojas and D’Arcy 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Villasenor, J." box="[349,533,1212,1239]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" pagination="559 - 902" refId="ref7168" refString="Villasenor, J. (2016) Checklist of the native vascular plants of Mexico. Revista Mexicana de Biodiversidad 87: 559 - 902. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. rmb. 2016.06.017" type="journal article" year="2016">Villaseñor 2016</bibRefCitation>
). With further study, this name may be synonymized with the South American 
<taxonomicName authority="(Rusby 1896: 90) Bitter (1919: 439)" authorityName="Bitter" authorityPageNumber="439" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="Rusby" baseAuthorityPageNumber="90" baseAuthorityYear="1896" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycianthes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="inaequilatera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">L. inaequilatera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rusby, H." box="[302,482,1248,1274]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 130" refId="ref6992" refString="Rusby, H. (1896) An enumeration of the plants collected in Bolivia by Miguel Bang, Part III. Memoirs of the Torrey Botanical Club 6: 1 - 130." type="journal article" year="1896">Rusby 1896: 90</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Bitter, G." box="[497,702,1248,1274]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40" pagination="292 - 520" refId="ref6023" refString="Bitter, G. (1919) Die Gattung Lycianthes. Abhandlungen Herausgegeban vom Naturwissenschaftlichen Verein zu Bremen 24: 292 - 520." type="journal article" year="1919">Bitter (1919: 439)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
